==Useful Info==
The '''ice dragon''' is a moderately powerful [[dragon]] capable of breathing deadly bolts of [[cold]] (3d24), which can knock you back if you are flying. Not surprisingly, they are highly resistant to cold damage, but vulnerable to [[fire]]. They appear commonly in the lower floors of the [[Dungeon]], the [[Depths]], and [[the Realm of Zot]], but can show up dangerously [[out of depth]] in [[vault]]s as early as [[the Lair]] or certain versions of the [[Ice cave]].

{{monster spells}}

==Tips & Tricks==
*If you find one early on, escaping is a good idea. Without at least rC+ for its breath and decent AC for its melee attacks, they can do immense damage to low- or mid-level characters.
*[[Fire Magic]] and [[flaming]] weapons will deal extra damage to ice dragons.
*Killing an ice dragon may provide [[ice dragon scales]], a medium-weight set of armour that provides excellent cold resistance at the cost of fire vulnerability.
